text:
South Winneshiek comes out over Jesup with a 24-13 win - KWWL - Eastern Iowa Breaking News, Weather, Closings Member Center: South Winneshiek comes out over Jesup with a 24-13 win Posted: Friday Night Heroes Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> 
Jesup playing host to South Winn. Jesup comes in with a 3-2 record after thrashing MFL Mar Mac while tenth ranked South Winn crushed Sumner-Fredericsburg 48-8. 
After a slow start in the first quarter, the warriors heat up. 
Ben Meyer starts the drive with a jet sweep, bringing the warriors about a yard away from the end zone. 
South Winneshiek finishes strong, with big Carson Lensing pushing through for the score... Giving the warriors the 6-0 lead. 
Speaking of Lensing, look at this play... Taking the sweep and making the cut to reverse the field. Lensing powers through a defender to give the warriors a first down. 
Late in the second quarter, jesup punts inside their own twenty as Ben Meyer takes the punt... Fifty yards to give the warriors great field position. 
Meyer takes advantage of his big return with a one yard score, putting the warriors up 12-0. 
South Winneshiek would go on to win this one handily 24-13. Can't Find Something? 500 Fourth St. Waterloo, IA 50703 News: (319) 291-1200
